summary: CAS number not shown on induced mutation search page
Steps_to_Reproduce:
Steps to verify:
1.	Login and select Submit Models
2.	If you do not have a model to use, select Add New Model and fill in the required fields on the Model Characteristics page
3.	Select Genetic Description from the left menu bar, and then select Enter Induced Mutation.
4.	Fill in all the required fields along with CAS.  (Note: Simply add a value of your choice (For example 50-81-7 is the CAS number for Ascorbic acid and the users will be able to get this from the link).
5.	Select the Submit button on the bottom of the page.
6.	If you see the Notice that says:  This model's status is currently set to Incomplete, select the Set Model status to complete button.
7.	Go to the Admin section from the button on the top of the page (talk to us if you DO NOT have this button)
8.	Select Assign.   Submit that screen.
9.	Select Approve. - Submit that screen
10.	Select link to Assign an Editor  Submit that screen
11.	Select link to Approve Model  Submit that screen
12.	Now you can go to Search Models and enter the name of your model in the Model Name / Model Descriptor field.
13.	Select you model from the list (most likely the list is short)
14.	Select the Genetic Description and find the data under Induced Mutation data

summary: Mapping issues
Steps_to_Reproduce:
Testing steps.  Basically we're creating Taxon objects, but we should never delete them.  They're created in three places:

1) The model characteristics page (species and strain)
2) Engineered Transgene
3) Xenograft

Select the number of Taxon objects in the database.  (i.e. select count(*) from taxon)
Create entries for all three of these, do not select Other.
Duplicate the model.
Select the number of Taxon objects in the database.  It should be the same.
Delete both models.
Select the number of Taxon objects in the database.  It should be the same.

Create a model, but select Other where appropriate.  Make sure the Other value selected does not already exist in the database.
Verify that it creates new entries.
Duplicate the model.
Delete both models.
Validate that the Taxon entries are still there.

summary: EVS Tree - restore the association between organ and diagnosis
Steps_to_Reproduce:
n/a
For information about the mouse vocabularies used go to http://nciterms.nci.nih.gov
Hit the connect button

Path to mouse anatomy: 
Experimental Organism Anatomical Concept --&gt; Murine Tissue Type 

Path to mouse diseases: 
Experimental Organism Diagnosis --&gt; Mouse Pathologic Diagnoses --&gt; Mouse Disorder by Site 

Path to human anatomy:
Anatomic Structure, System, or Substance --&gt; use organ and association with organ system (Anatomic_Structure_is_Physical_Part_of )

Path to human diagnoses:
Disease, Disorder or Finding --&gt; Diseases and Disorders --&gt; Disorder by Site (Disease_Has_Associated_Anatomic_Site )
